headline: 1 Mid-Cap Stock Worth Investigating and 2 We Ignore
summary: Mid-cap stocks often strike the right balance between having proven business models and market opportunities that can support $100 billion corporations. However, they face intense competition from scaled industry giants and can be disrupted by new innovative players vying for a slice of the pie.

headline: Multi-million-dollar manufacturing expansions planned in Decatur
summary: Nov. 20—Two Decatur companies will pursue a combined $37.6 million in expansions, with one bringing at least 40 new jobs to the area. M&J Industries Inc. and the J.M. Smucker Co. shared plans for expansion with the Decatur Industrial Development Board on Tuesday, during which time the two companies presented four separate requests for tax abatements.
